DPA-025","rule_version":"1.0.0"}],"findings":[{"description":"No license grant or prohibited-uses enumeration was found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"An EULA without an explicit grant defaults to copyright law's narrow defaults; without prohibited uses, abuse vectors are unaddressed.","id":"ADDENDA-017-s1-0","recommendation":"State the grant ('non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable license to use the Software'); enumerate prohibited uses (reverse engineer, sublicense, competitive benchmarking).","rule_id":"ADDENDA-017","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"addenda-eu-digital-content-directive-2019-770","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"EU Digital Content Directive 2019/770","source_url":"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/eli/dir/2019/770/oj"}],"title":"License grant scope / prohibited uses missing"},{"description":"The document references fees but no 'Net X' or 'due within' clause was found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no payment-term clause)"},"explanation":"Commercial contracts should state when payment is due. 'Net 30' or 'due within X days of invoice' is the typical formulation. Without it, payment timing defaults to the governing-law rule.","id":"FIN-005-s1-0","rule_id":"FIN-005","rule_version":"1.4.2","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No payment-term clause detected"},{"description":"The contract does not allocate ownership of intellectual property.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no IP-ownership clause)"},"explanation":"Without an IP-ownership clause, default copyright and patent rules apply: under 17 U.S.C. § 201, copyright vests in the author/employee unless work-for-hire or assignment applies.","id":"IPDATA-001-s1-0","rule_id":"IPDATA-001","rule_version":"1.2.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"stat-17-usc-101","license":"Public domain (US government work)","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-11T00:00:00Z","source":"17 U.S.C. § 101 — Definitions (work made for hire)","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/17/101"},{"id":"stat-17-usc-201","license":"Public domain (US government work)","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-11T00:00:00Z","source":"17 U.S.C. § 201","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/17/201"}],"title":"No IP-ownership clause detected"},{"description":"Neither 'indemnify' nor 'hold harmless' appears in the document.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no indemnification language)"},"explanation":"Most commercial contracts allocate risk through an indemnification clause. The absence leaves the parties to default tort and contract law for any third-party claims.","id":"RISK-001-s1-0","rule_id":"RISK-001","rule_version":"1.1.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No indemnification clause detected"},{"description":"No Effective Date is named, defined, or stated near the top of this Agreement.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no Effective Date reference matched)"},"explanation":"Most contracts identify a starting point that other date references rely on. Without it, relative terms like 'within 30 days after the Effective Date' have no anchor.","id":"STRUCT-002-s1-0","recommendation":"Add an Effective Date — either in the preamble ('dated as of [date]'), as a defined term, or as an explicit 'Effective Date: [date]' line.","rule_id":"STRUCT-002","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No Effective Date found"},{"description":"No reference to EU consumer-law minimums (Digital Content Directive 2019/770 or CRD 2011/83) was found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"EU consumer law cannot be contracted around for consumer-facing EULAs.","id":"ADDENDA-018-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: 'Nothing in this EULA limits the consumer rights conferred by Directive (EU) 2019/770 on digital content or Directive 2011/83/EU on consumer rights.'","rule_id":"ADDENDA-018","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"addenda-eu-digital-content-directive-2019-770","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"EU Digital Content Directive 2019/770","source_url":"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/eli/dir/2019/770/oj"}],"title":"EU consumer-law minimums missing"},{"description":"LICENSOR'S TOTAL CUMULATIVE LIABILITY ARISING OUT OF OR RELATING TO THIS EULA, WHETHER IN CONTRACT, TORT (INCLUDING NEGL","document_position":2880,"excerpt":{"end_offset":3183,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":2880,"text":"LICENSOR'S TOTAL CUMULATIVE LIABILITY ARISING OUT OF OR RELATING TO THIS EULA, WHETHER IN CONTRACT, TORT (INCLUDING NEGLIGENCE), OR OTHERWISE, SHALL NOT EXCEED THE LICENSE FEES ACTUALLY PAID BY END USER TO LICENSOR DURING THE TWELVE (12) MONTHS IMMEDIATELY PRECEDING THE EVENT GIVING RISE TO THE CLAIM."},"explanation":"Negative covenants restrict what a party may do. Surfacing them collectively makes it easier to check they are intended and consistent with the overall deal.","id":"OBLI-005-s1-2880","rule_id":"OBLI-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Negative covenants: 1"},{"description":"One party retains sole discretion over a stated determination.","document_position":1454,"excerpt":{"end_offset":1476,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":1454,"text":"5. Updates and Upgrades. Licensor may, in its sole discretion, provide updates, patches, or new versions of the Software (\"Updates\"). Updates shall be subject to the terms of this EULA unless accompa"},"explanation":"Sole-discretion clauses give one party unilateral power. They are bounded by the implied duty of good faith and fair dealing (Restatement (Second) of Contracts § 205), but the language is asymmetric and worth a deliberate review.","id":"OBLI-006-s1-1454","rule_id":"OBLI-006","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"stat-restatement-205-good-faith","license":"Public domain (US government work)","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-11T00:00:00Z","source":"Restatement (Second) of Contracts § 205 (Duty of Good Faith and Fair Dealing)","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/wex/good_faith"}],"title":"'In its sole discretion' clause present"},{"description":"LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, EXEMPLARY, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES","document_position":2569,"excerpt":{"end_offset":2660,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":2569,"text":"7. Limitation of Liability. TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, IN NO EVENT SHALL LICENSOR BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, EXEMPLARY, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, INCLUDING LOST PROFITS, LOSS OF DATA, "},"explanation":"A waiver of consequential, special, incidental, and punitive damages is standard in commercial contracts. The waiver should be mutual unless deliberately asymmetric.","id":"RISK-007-s1-2569","rule_id":"RISK-007","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Consequential damages waiver present"},{"description":"The following defined terms are never used outside their definition: EAR.","document_position":4118,"excerpt":{"end_offset":4125,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":4118,"text":"EAR"},"explanation":"Defined terms that are not used downstream may be inherited from a template and obsolete. They clutter the contract and can confuse readers; either delete them or use them where intended.","id":"STRUCT-005-s1-4118","recommendation":"Review each unused term and either delete it or wire it into the relevant clause.","rule_id":"STRUCT-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Defined terms with no uses: 1"},{"description":"Upon termination, End User must immediately cease all use of the Software and destroy","document_position":3540,"excerpt":{"end_offset":3625,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":3540,"text":"8. Termination. This EULA is effective until terminated. Licensor may terminate this EULA immediately upon written notice if End User breaches any term of this EULA and fails to cure such breach within thirty (30) days of written notice from Licensor. End User may terminate this "},"explanation":"Post-termination obligations typically include return or destruction of confidential materials, deletion of data, and a certificate of destruction.","id":"TERM-007-s1-3540","rule_id":"TERM-007","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Post-termination obligations enumerated"}],"playbook_id":"eula","playbook_match_confidence":1,"playbook_match_reasoning":"forced via sidecar to eula","result_hash":"38ce6c14f5c59789cabd13af96ff4496f78400d5d5c663a751f958e6ddba338d","source_file":{"name":"eula-no-license-grant-or-prohibitions-fail.txt","sha256":"869ddab874471a5a80a0f3c7c917e3ab932cbf47fd880ad59b4b349979e1e26e","size_bytes":1},"version":"9.41.0"}